{
    "attributes": {
        "action": "Write off student loans for nurses trained after 2016",
        "additional_details": "In 2016, the NHS Bursary Scheme was removed, leaving nursing students to fund their education through loans. We feel this has created inequality between nurses trained before and after 2016, and, with ongoing NHS staffing shortages, may discourage people from entering or staying in the profession. We believe writing off this debt would support recruitment, improve retention, and recognise the vital role nurses play.",
        "background": "Since the NHS Bursary was removed in 2016, nursing students have taken on significant student debt. We believe this creates inequality & may discourage people entering or staying in the profession \u2013 writing off this debt would support recruitment, improve retention & recognise nurses\u2019 contribution.",
